      "writtenOn": "2020-08-11T08:20:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It sounds fine to provide testing.ServiceState.Log. Let me do that.\n\nHowever I still think providing a service-scoped context is aligned to the overall context/state design in Tast --- for every entity (test/precondition/fixture/service) we want to consistently provide context and state tied to the entity and its lifetime. Currently the only context.Context available to services are ones passed to gRPC methods, which are requested-scoped (and thus canceled after a gRPC method call finishes).",
